  "pr_number": 15043,
  "issue_number": 15042,
  "issue_title": "[Bug]: Custom base_url is inconsistently resolved when model instance region is empty",
  "issue_body": "### Self Checks\n\n- [x] I have searched for existing issues [search for existing issues](https://github.com/infiniflow/ragflow/issues), including closed ones.\n- [x] I confirm that I am using English to submit this report ([Language Policy](https://github.com/infiniflow/ragflow/issues/5910)).\n- [x] Non-english title submitions will be closed directly ( \u975e\u82f1\u6587\u6807\u9898\u7684\u63d0\u4ea4\u5c06\u4f1a\u88ab\u76f4\u63a5\u5173\u95ed ) ([Language Policy](https://github.com/infiniflow/ragflow/issues/5910)).\n- [x] Please do not modify this template :) and fill in all the required fields.\n\n### RAGFlow workspace code commit ID\n\n`6499bce2a67c55191efb7dc4cfe3ff359b64c5ef`\n\n### RAGFlow image version\n\n`main` branch at commit `6499bce2a67c55191efb7dc4cfe3ff359b64c5ef`; not image-version specific.\n\n### Other environment information\n\n- Hardware parameters: N/A\n- OS type: N/A\n- Others: Reproducible from the Go source code in `internal/service/model_service.go` and `internal/entity/models/*.go`.\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nCustom `base_url` handling for Go model drivers is inconsistent when a model instance has no configured region.\n\nAfter #15030, `ModelProviderService` creates request-local drivers through `newModelDriverForBaseURL`. The helper preserves the configured region key:\n\n```go\nnewDriver := driver.NewInstance(map[string]string{\n    region: baseURL,\n})\n```\n\nAt the service call sites, `region` comes from `extra[\"region\"]` and is also assigned to `apiConfig.Region`:\n\n```go\nregion := extra[\"region\"]\napiConfig.Region = &region\n```\n\nWhen `extra[\"region\"]` is missing or empty, the request-local driver's base URL map is keyed by the empty string:\n\n```go\nBaseURL[\"\"] = customBaseURL\n```\n\nSome driver methods then preserve the empty region and read `BaseURL[\"\"]`, so the custom URL works. Examples:\n\n- `internal/entity/models/openai.go`: `ChatWithMessages` and `ListModels`\n- `internal/entity/models/ollama.go`: synchronous `ChatWithMessages`\n- `internal/entity/models/lmstudio.go`: synchronous `ChatWithMessages`\n\nOther driver methods normalize an empty region to `\"default\"` before looking up the base URL, so they read `BaseURL[\"default\"]` instead. Examples:\n\n- `internal/entity/models/openai.go`: streaming chat and embedding paths\n- `internal/entity/models/vllm.go`: chat, streaming chat, embedding, list models, and check connection paths\n- `internal/entity/models/localai.go`: paths using `resolveBaseURL`\n- `internal/entity/models/xinference.go`: paths using `xinferenceRegion` / `baseURLForRegion`\n- `internal/entity/models/ollama.go` and `internal/entity/models/lmstudio.go`: streaming, embedding, and list models paths\n\nFor those `\"default\"` lookup paths, a custom `base_url` configured without a region can be ignored or reported as missing even though the service already supplied it under `BaseURL[\"\"]`.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nA custom `base_url` with no explicit region should resolve consistently across all methods of a provider.\n\nEither the service should provide a default-region fallback for empty-region custom URLs, or all drivers should consistently use the same empty-region lookup convention.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Use `main` at commit `6499bce2a67c55191efb7dc4cfe3ff359b64c5ef`.\n2. Configure a model instance with `extra.base_url` set and no `extra.region` value.\n3. Trigger a method whose driver normalizes empty region to `\"default\"`, for example a VLLM custom-base-url chat/list path, an OpenAI-compatible streaming/embedding path, or a LocalAI/Xinference path.\n4. Observe from `internal/service/model_service.go` that the request-local driver is created with `map[string]string{\"\": baseURL}`.\n5. Observe from the affected driver method that it resolves the empty `apiConfig.Region` as `\"default\"` and then looks up `BaseURL[\"default\"]`.\n6. The configured custom URL is not available under the key the driver uses.\n\n### Additional information\n\nThis is a follow-up to #15030. That PR intentionally preserved the old `map[string]string{region: baseURL}` behavior while adding nil guards for `NewInstance`, because changing the empty region key to only `\"default\"` would have regressed drivers that still look up `BaseURL[\"\"]`.\n\nThe remaining issue is the cross-driver empty-region contract: some paths use `\"\"`, while others use `\"default\"`.\n\nI searched open and closed issues for related terms including `custom base_url empty region`, `BaseURL default region`, `base_url region default`, and `NewInstance base_url region`, and did not find a matching issue.\n",
